The paper proposes a technique to improve the generalization performance of deep networks trained on corrupted training data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses on deep neural networks, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories.
